# what is redis and how to use it
redis is an in memory key-value noSQL database
it has super fast read&wirte because data is stored dirctly on RAM rather on the Disk
most of the time it is used for caching and saving users sessions
here is some of commands on how to use redis after installing :

	zerobors@void-linux ~ Â» redis-cli
	127.0.0.1:6379> SET name 'Ehab'
	OK
	127.0.0.1:6379> get name
	"Ehab"

you can delete keys:
	127.0.0.1:6379> DEL name
	(integer) 1
	127.0.0.1:6379> get name
	(nil)
	127.0.0.1:6379>

you can also set expire time for the keys
	127.0.0.1:6379> SET name 'ehab'
	OK
	127.0.0.1:6379> EXPIRE name 10
	(integer) 1
	127.0.0.1:6379> get name
	"ehab"
#wait 10 seconds
	127.0.0.1:6379> get name
	(nil)
	127.0.0.1:6379>



